An advocate [/b]is one who devotes themself to the study of Sigil's laws, making sense of the labyrinthine structure of legalities that hold the city together. They can represent a person in a court of law, draw up legacies (also called "wills"), and perform other tasks that mark one's citizenship in a society.</p>
Source[/b]
In the Cage: A Guide to Sigil    
